<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-05-02T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-05-02T13:00:00-05:00" n="628" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d628">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">814.00/1199: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Hanna</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-05-02T12:00:00-06:00">May 2,
                                1935—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 2:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>17. Department’s telegram No. 11, April 30, 6 p.m. The Department’s view
                            of my conversations is correct. I have no valid reason to think that the
                            second impression mentioned in the last paragraph of the telegram exists
                            in Government circles here. I would like therefore, before taking any
                            steps in the sense indicated by the Department, to obtain the
                            Department’s views on one or two specific points which I will submit by
                            next air mail.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hanna</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>